-- Murdoch Plans $1-a-Week Tablet-Only U.S. Newspaper, Financial Review Says
-- B y   R o b e r t   F e n n e r
-- 2010-11-05T02:36:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/murdoch-plans-1-a-week-tablet-only-u-s-newspaper-financial-review-says.html
News Corp. plans to start a daily
U.S. “newspaper” in six weeks time that will only be available
on tablet computers, the Australian Financial Review reported,
citing an interview with Chairman  Rupert Murdoch .  To be known as “The Daily” and edited by New York Post
deputy editor  Jesse Angelo , the new paper will charge $1 a week
and is aiming for about 800,000 subscribers, according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Robert Fenner  in Sydney 
